Compass (with blueprint)and fancy buttons

/Gemfile (Add)
gem "compass", ">= 0.10.2"
gem "fancy-buttons"

$> compass init rails -r fancy-buttons -f fancy-buttons --using blueprint --force

(Respond yes to both questions)

Create a file /app/views/stylesheets/buttons.scss
  @import "page-styles";
  @import "fancy-buttons";

  button {@include fancy-button}

Add to layout files
%head
  / *************************************************************************
  / these lines are to get working fancybuttons http://brandonmathis.com/projects/fancy-buttons/
  / *************************************************************************
  /[if lt IE 7]
    = stylesheet_link_tag 'compiled/ie6.css', :media => 'screen, projection'
  = stylesheet_link_tag 'compiled/buttons.css', :media => 'screen, projection'

  / *************************************************************************
  / these ones are to get BluePrint CSS Framework through compass
  / ************************************************************************* 
  = stylesheet_link_tag 'compiled/screen.css', :media => 'screen, projection'
  = stylesheet_link_tag 'compiled/print.css', :media => 'print'
  /[if IE]
    = stylesheet_link_tag 'compiled/ie.css', :media => 'screen, projection'


(Remember that blueprint into compass has a limited scope, so to use it 
we have to scope the use of blueprint, for example:
  %body.bp)

Restart the server
